{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781719577059,"sessionID":"ses_1293d8f5cffeM0kbBvfYyfngHB","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"glob","callID":"call_00_yLILNWMic0qvNr5kQgEc8288","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit","pattern":"**/bin/**\""},"output":"No files found","metadata":{"count":0,"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit","time":{"start":1781719577030,"end":1781719577058}},"id":"prt_ed6c33002001kV3d767peSEuQ3","sessionID":"ses_1293d8f5cffeM0kbBvfYyfngHB","messageID":"msg_ed6c324720013afmgmtu27LANc"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781719577687,"sessionID":"ses_1293d8f5cffeM0kbBvfYyfngHB","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_01_hl4kFKLUuuViNhoBeLf52177","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit","pattern":"maintenanceMarkerDir|stale-reclaim|dead-socket"},"output":"Found 6 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.6.0.0.md:\n  Line 49: Phase 019 brought the mk-skill-advisor launcher up to the resilience bar the spec-memory and code-index launchers reached in 026/027: an owner lease, a reconnecting session proxy, and — the piece that mattered most — acting on a dead-socket respawn decision instead of discarding it, so a hung daemon is reaped and replaced under a bootstrap lock rather than leaving a session stranded or spawning a second writer.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/model-server-respawn-lock-atomic.vitest.ts:\n  Line 4: // Regression for the respawn-lock stale-reclaim race: a bare unlink+open is not\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.5.0.4.md:\n  Line 23: | **The audit closed the rest** | An eleven-lineage multi-model review serialized the stale-reclaim reap under the respawn lock, then replaced it with true adoption: a fresh session bridges a live released daemon instead of reaping it, and reaps only a dead one. The release path also SIGKILL-escalates a wedged sidecar, and a tracked local settings file that leaked personal permissions was untracked. |\n\n  Line 101: The reap-before-respawn fix had claimed the owner-lease acquisition as its spawn mutex. That holds only when no prior lease exists. Reclaiming a stale owner lease, left by an owner that crashed without releasing, is a non-exclusive write, so two fresh launchers racing it could both reap and respawn. The stale-reclaim reap and spawn now run under the same exclusive respawn lock the dead-socket path already uses, and the loser bails and reconnects.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature_catalog/14--pipeline-architecture/lease-probe-retry-reap-hardening.md:\n  Line 52: | `mcp_server/tests/launcher-reap-hardening.vitest.ts` | Automated test | Unit-tests consecutive-failure reaping, alive-result short-circuit, the configurable retry budget and dead-socket fast-fail |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/README.md:\n  Line 1070: | [`references/config/launcher_lease.md`](./references/config/launcher_lease.md)                   | mk-spec-memory launcher single-writer lease and stale-reclaim behavior                               |\n","metadata":{"matches":6,"truncated":false},"title":"maintenanceMarkerDir|stale-reclaim|dead-socket","time":{"start":1781719577633,"end":1781719577685}},"id":"prt_ed6c3320c00132E1pDI6gbNPKZ","sessionID":"ses_1293d8f5cffeM0kbBvfYyfngHB","messageID":"msg_ed6c324720013afmgmtu27LANc"}}
